3.187 
Property of minor children not subject to usufruct 
Parents may not exercise usufruct over the property of their minor children which is: 
1) acquired by the child with his/her own earnings; 
2) intended for the child's education, the pursuit of his/her interests or the organisation of his/her leisure time; 
3) given to the child as a gift or inherited by the child, provided that the property is not subject to the imposition of a usufruct. Art.
